# 🔥 1. Cluster Setup & Core Concepts (Warm-up but essential)

### Task

* Spin up a cluster using:

  * `kubeadm` OR
  * Kind / Minikube (fast practice)

### What to practice

* Configure:

  * Pod CIDR
  * CNI (Calico / Flannel)
* Verify:

  * Nodes, components, kube-system pods

### Interview twist

> “Cluster is up but CoreDNS is not working — debug it.”

---

# ⚙️ 2. Application Deployment (Real-world microservice)

### Task

Deploy a 3-tier app:

* Frontend (nginx or react app)
* Backend (Node.js / Python API)
* Database (MySQL / PostgreSQL)

### Requirements

* Use:

  * Deployments
  * Services (ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer)
* Add:

  * ConfigMaps
  * Secrets

### Interview twist

> “App is deployed but frontend can’t reach backend — debug networking.”

---

# 🌐 3. Networking Deep Dive

### Task

* Implement:

  * ClusterIP
  * Headless service
  * Ingress (NGINX Ingress Controller)

### Advanced

* Add:

  * Path-based routing
  * TLS (self-signed cert)

### Troubleshooting scenario

> “Ingress is created but not accessible from browser.”

---

# 📦 4. Storage (Very Frequently Asked)

### Task

* Create:

  * PersistentVolume (PV)
  * PersistentVolumeClaim (PVC)
* Attach to DB pod

### Advanced

* Use:

  * Dynamic provisioning (StorageClass)

### Interview twist

> “Pod is stuck in Pending due to PVC — debug it.”

---

# 🔐 5. Security (CRITICAL for senior roles)

### Task

* Create:

  * RBAC roles & role bindings
* Restrict:

  * Namespace access for a user

### Advanced

* Implement:

  * Network Policies (deny all → allow specific)

### Scenario

> “Developer has access to cluster but cannot list pods — fix it.”

---

# 📊 6. Monitoring & Logging

### Task

* Install:

  * Prometheus
  * Grafana

### Practice

* Create alert:

  * Pod restart > threshold

### Logging

* Use:

  * EFK stack OR simple `kubectl logs`

### Scenario

> “Pod is restarting randomly — how do you debug?”

---

# 🚀 7. CI/CD Integration

### Task

* Build pipeline using:

  * Jenkins / GitHub Actions

### Flow

* Build Docker image
* Push to registry
* Deploy to K8s

### Advanced

* Implement:

  * Rolling updates
  * Rollbacks

### Scenario

> “New deployment broke production — rollback fast.”

---

# ⚖️ 8. Scaling & Performance

### Task

* Configure:

  * HPA (Horizontal Pod Autoscaler)

### Based on

* CPU / memory

### Advanced

* VPA (if possible)

### Scenario

> “Traffic spike — app is slow. Fix using autoscaling.”

